Melania and Donald Trump extend their greetings to Muslims in the United States and around the world for the celebration of Eid al-Fitr. They acknowledge the significance of Eid as a time for reflection and a return to daily life with renewed joy and love for others. They emphasize the importance of forgiveness and building strong relationships within and among communities. The statement also highlights the role of religion in America's history and the lives of the faithful. The Trumps express hope that the spirit of peace and goodwill that accompanies Eid continues throughout the year and worldwide. They wish all Muslims a happy Eid al-Fitr.